        "synopsis": {
            "value": "Hyun Min-Cheol (Ji Hyun-Woo) grew up in an orphanage and he was barely able to support himself by doing labor work. But, with a strong conviction and perseverance, he eventually rose all the way to become the president elect of South Korea. His wife is Cha Soo-Yeon (Eugene). With 67 days remaining until his presidential inauguration, he suddenly demands a divorce from Cha Soo-Yeon, who has waited to become the first lady. As the  presidential inauguration date gets closer, political conspiracies and family secrets are revealed amid a suffocating conflict between Hyun Min-Cheol and Cha Soo-Yeon.",
            "source": "asianwiki"
